ion asymmetry of a linearly\npolarised gamma-ray beam in the low energy pair creation regime. This sub-GeV\nenergy range is critical for cosmic sources as their spectra are power laws\nwhich fall quickly as a function of increasing energy.\n  This work could pave the way to extending polarised gamma-ray astronomy\nbeyond the MeV energy regime.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 20 Jun 2017 14:33:59 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 30 Aug 2017 11:18:48 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-10-26"}
